<paragraph blockId="9.[189,303,1903,1929]" box="[189,303,1903,1929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1903,1929]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1903,1929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1398,1949,2011]" lastBlockId="10.[189,1399,267,611]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
This monotypic genus was placed in Penthimiini by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans J. W." box="[840,1003,1949,1975]" firstAuthor="Evans" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Entomological Society of London" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="105 - 271" part="98" refId="ref48943" refString="Evans J. W. 1947. A natural classification of leaf-hoppers (Jassoidea, Homoptera). Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 98: 105 - 271. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1947. tb 01054. x" title="A natural classification of leaf-hoppers (Jassoidea, Homoptera)" type="journal article" year="1947">Evans (1947)</bibRefCitation>
but later returned to Ledrini by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans J. W." box="[189,349,1984,2011]" firstAuthor="Evans" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar Tananarive (E" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="87 - 137" part="4" refId="ref48993" refString="Evans J. W. 1953. Les Cicadellidae de Madagascar. Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar Tananarive (E) 4: 87 - 137." title="Les Cicadellidae de Madagascar" type="journal article" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones J. R. &amp; Deitz L. L." box="[359,609,1984,2011]" firstAuthor="Jones" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 120" part="2186" refId="ref49082" refString="Jones J. R. &amp; Deitz L. L. 2009. Phylogeny and systematics of the leafhopper subfamily Ledrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa 2186 (1): 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2186.1.1" title="Phylogeny and systematics of the leafhopper subfamily Ledrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae)" type="journal article" year="2009">Jones &amp; Deitz (2009)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a genus 
<emphasis box="[851,1012,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">incertae sedis</emphasis>
because their morphology-based phylogenetic analysis failed to support its inclusion in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1855" box="[839,947,267,293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ledrinae">Ledrinae</taxonomicName>
. The genus is known only from a few very old museum specimens and was not encountered in the recent extensive terrrestrial arthropod inventory of 
<collectingCountry box="[347,491,338,364]" name="Madagascar" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirkaldy" authorityYear="1903" box="[696,831,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Betsileonas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[696,831,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Betsileonas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now either extremely rare or extinct. Males remain unknown, but several characters mentioned or illustrated for the genus by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones J. R. &amp; Deitz L. L." box="[1147,1398,373,399]" firstAuthor="Jones" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 120" part="2186" refId="ref49082" refString="Jones J. R. &amp; Deitz L. L. 2009. Phylogeny and systematics of the leafhopper subfamily Ledrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa 2186 (1): 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2186.1.1" title="Phylogeny and systematics of the leafhopper subfamily Ledrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae)" type="journal article" year="2009">Jones &amp; Deitz (2009)</bibRefCitation>
support its placement in 
<taxonomicName authority="Dietrich &amp; Magalhães &amp; Takiya, 2020" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Magalhães &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2020" box="[475,613,408,434]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Platyjassini" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Platyjassini</taxonomicName>
, including the spatulate head with dorsal ocelli well separated from the crown apex, the rugose texture on the crown, the anterolateral extensions of the vertex overlapping the eyes, and the distally fused RP and MA in the hindwing. The ovipositor structure also resembles that of some other 
<taxonomicName authority="Dietrich &amp; Magalhães &amp; Takiya, 2020" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Magalhães &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2020" box="[363,502,514,540]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Platyjassini" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Platyjassini</taxonomicName>
. Known from a single species, the genus is easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName authority="Dietrich &amp; Magalhães &amp; Takiya, 2020" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Magalhães &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,324,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Platyjassini" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Platyjassini</taxonomicName>
by its very large size (length 
<quantity box="[668,798,549,576]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="17.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="15.0">15–19 mm</quantity>
), the head being distinctly wider than the pronotum and its marmorate dorsal color pattern (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones J. R. &amp; Deitz L. L." box="[698,935,584,611]" firstAuthor="Jones" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 120" part="2186" refId="ref49082" refString="Jones J. R. &amp; Deitz L. L. 2009. Phylogeny and systematics of the leafhopper subfamily Ledrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa 2186 (1): 1 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2186.1.1" title="Phylogeny and systematics of the leafhopper subfamily Ledrinae (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae)" type="journal article" year="2009">Jones &amp; Deitz 2009</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 5c).
</paragraph>
